The red-crowned crane is the largest animal on the Red Beach Wetland. In February and March, these big birds leave their wintering ground and return to the beach. Watch the video to know more about the life of these graceful "dancers" on the red beach. About 'Journeys in Nature': Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series With a coastline that stretches over 1,200 kilometers, Liaodong Bay is the northernmost bay in China. It is covered in thick ice throughout winter to early spring. It is still full of life. This series explores the animal species and their unique ways of surviving in the bay. For more: Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 1: A red paradise (Cover image via video screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)